        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 21 at 3:54PM CDT by NWS Mobile AL</headline>
        <description>At 354 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles east of Jay, or 13 miles south of Brewton, moving southwest at
5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northwestern Santa
Rosa County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
